KudoProfile is the page where you configure your Kudocracy identity for SimpliWiki.

Your KudoProfile contains:

GitHub Identity: Your authenticated GitHub login (e.g., @jhr)
Kudocracy Name: The name used in Kudocracy contexts (e.g., @jhr)

Why two names?
GitHub provides secure authentication via OAuth.
Kudocracy Name provides identity when embedding SimpliWiki via ?kudocracy= parameter.

The Kudocracy Name is configurable and separate from GitHub, but traceable to your GitHub account for accountability.

How to change your Kudocracy Name:
Visit /kudo-profile in your SimpliWiki installation.
Enter your desired name (must start with @, 1-15 alphanumeric characters).
Click "Set Kudocracy Name".

The name will be stored in a cookie and used when generating Kudocracy contexts for embedded SimpliWiki instances.

Technical Details:
Context generation uses lib/kudocracy.js
Cookie: sw_kudo_twitter_name
Session property: session.kudoTwitterName

